net.doo.snap.chequescanner

Class ChequeScannerFrameHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.doo.snap.chequescanner.ChequeScannerFrameHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PreviewBuffer.FrameHandler

    public class ChequeScannerFrameHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements PreviewBuffer.FrameHandler
    Performs cheque data detection on camera preview frames. Outputs results via ChequeScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler (addResultHandler(ResultHandler)).

    Preview frame considered intercepted if at least one ChequeScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler returns true from ChequeScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler.handleResult(Result)

    See Also:
    PreviewBuffer

        public boolean handleFrame(PreviewBuffer.FrameHandler.Frame previewFrame)
        Description copied from interface: PreviewBuffer.FrameHandler
        Invoked for every new camera preview frame
        Specified by:
        handleFrame in interface PreviewBuffer.FrameHandler
        Parameters:
        previewFrame - captured preview frame data
        Returns:
        true if frame should be considered as "intercepted", i.e. no further processing should be performed on it. false to allow other frame handlers to process this frame.

      • addResultHandler

        public void addResultHandler(ChequeScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler handler)
        Registers result handler which will be notified about cheque data detection results.

        Results are coming on the worker thread. Don't forget to move execution to main thread before updating UI.

        Parameters:
        handler - handler to register. Must not be null. If handler was already registered, nothing happens.

      • removeResultHandler

        public void removeResultHandler(ChequeScannerFrameHandler.ResultHandler handler)
        Unregisters handler.
        Parameters:
        handler - handler to unregister. If it was not registered before, nothing happens.

      • isEnabled

        public boolean isEnabled()
        Returns:
        true if cheque data detection is enabled. false if cheque data detection is disabled, i.e. incoming frames are skipped.

      • setEnabled

        public void setEnabled(boolean enabled)
        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enable cheque data detection. false to disable cheque data detection.
